## Infostyle Rules

- Write one thought per sentence
- Remove filler words (e.g., "literally", "actually", "just", "quite", "sort of" — adapt to target language equivalents)
- Focus on reader: use "you" perspective over "we guarantee" statements
- Use active voice: "We process" > "It is processed"
- Explain technical terms in context: provide translation or explanation in target language when needed
- Use en-dash "–" (U+2013), never em-dash "—" (U+2014)

